# Loading spatial / graphical libraries
library(gstat)

library(RColorBrewer)
library(tmap)
# import data 
SIA_SWO  <-  read.table(file = "results_mixsiar_drivers.csv", sep  = ";", header = T)

# Group prey 
prey_grouped <- SIA_SWO %>%
  mutate(
    fish = bathy + gadipela,
    ceph = cepha + cepha2) %>% 
  drop_na(ceph)

1 Load the models

# load models
fish <-  gam(fish ~ te(LON,LAT) + s(MLD,k=5) + SST, data=prey_grouped, family = betar(link = "logit"))

ceph = gam(ceph ~ te(LON, LAT) + s(LJFL, k = 5) + s(fishing_effort, k = 5) + SST, data=prey_grouped, family = betar(link = "logit")) 

gela1 = gam(gela ~ te(LON,LAT) + s(LJFL, k=5) + Chlmean + s(fishing_effort, k = 5), data=prey_grouped, family = betar(link = "logit"))

2 Load the grid for the prediction

grid <- st_read("drivers/grid_drivers.shp") %>% 
  mutate(Chlmean = chlmeanmea,
         depth = depth_mean,
         fishing_effort = FishingEff,
         SDO = sdomean,
         SST = sstmean,
         MLD = mldmean,
         LAT= centrdY,
         LON = centrdX,
         LJFL = 100)

3 Predict

ceph_pred <- predict(ceph, grid, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response") #type = "response" para que haga la transformacion con la funcion enlace logit

gela_pred <- predict(gela1, grid, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response") 

fish_pred <- predict(fish, grid, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response") 

pred <- data.frame(id = grid$id,
                   gela = gela_pred$fit,
                   fish = fish_pred$fit,
                   ceph = ceph_pred$fit,
                   sum = gela_pred$fit + fish_pred$fit + ceph_pred$fit) 

# merge to grid
grid_diet = merge(grid, pred, by  = "id")

4 Map the predition

# filter the cells you want to plot, only 2 away from data points (in qgis)
cells_to_pred <- read_csv("drivers/cells_to_pred.csv")

5 Project future diet

5.1 load SSPs scenarios

SSPs 2.6 and 8.5 for the 2090-2100 period (downloaded from BioOracle v3)

# Grid for the projection
grid_SSP26 <-  grid %>% 
  mutate(SST = sst_26_mea,
         Chlmean = chlmean_26,
         MLD = mld26_mean)   

grid_SSP85 <- grid %>% 
  mutate(SST = sst_85_mea,
         Chlmean = chlmean_85,
         MLD = mld85_mean)

5.2 Predict and project

ceph_now <- predict(ceph, grid, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response")

gela_now <- predict(gela1, grid, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response") 

fish_now <- predict(fish, grid, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response") 


# project to 2100
ceph_SSP26_2100 <- predict(ceph, grid_SSP26, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response")

gela_SSP26_2100 <- predict(gela1, grid_SSP26, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response") 

fish_SSP26_2100 <- predict(fish, grid_SSP26, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response") 

ceph_SSP85_2100 <- predict(ceph, grid_SSP85, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response")

gela_SSP85_2100 <- predict(gela1, grid_SSP85, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response") 

fish_SSP85_2100 <- predict(fish, grid_SSP85, se.fit = TRUE,type = "response")

pred2 <- data.frame(id = grid$id,
                   gela = gela_now$fit,

SST_min <- min(prey_grouped$SST, na.rm = TRUE)
SST_max <- max(prey_grouped$SST, na.rm = TRUE)

Chl_min <- min(prey_grouped$Chlmean, na.rm = TRUE)
Chl_max <- max(prey_grouped$Chlmean, na.rm = TRUE)

MLD_min <- min(prey_grouped$MLD, na.rm = TRUE)
MLD_max <- max(prey_grouped$MLD, na.rm = TRUE)

extrapolated_map  <- data.frame(id = grid$id,
                         SST_excess = ifelse(grid$SST < SST_min, - SST_min + grid$SST,
                                        ifelse(grid$SST > SST_max, grid$SST - SST_max, 0)),
                         CHL_excess = ifelse(grid$Chlmean < Chl_min, - Chl_min + grid$Chlmean,
                                        ifelse(grid$Chlmean > Chl_max, grid$Chlmean - Chl_max, 0)),
                         MLD_excess = ifelse(grid$MLD < MLD_min, - MLD_min + grid$MLD,
                                        ifelse(grid$MLD > MLD_max, grid$MLD - MLD_max, 0)),
                         SST26_excess = ifelse(grid$sst_26_mea < SST_min, - SST_min + grid$sst_26_mea,
                                        ifelse(grid$sst_26_mea > SST_max, grid$sst_26_mea - SST_max, 0)),
                         SST85_excess = ifelse(grid$sst_85_mea < SST_min, - SST_min + grid$sst_85_mea,
                                        ifelse(grid$sst_85_mea > SST_max, grid$sst_85_mea - SST_max, 0)),
                         CHL26_excess = ifelse(grid$chlmean_26 < Chl_min, - Chl_min + grid$chlmean_26,
                                        ifelse(grid$chlmean_26 > Chl_max, grid$chlmean_26 - Chl_max, 0)),
                         CHL85_excess = ifelse(grid$chlmean_85 < Chl_min, -Chl_min + grid$chlmean_85,
                                        ifelse(grid$chlmean_85 > Chl_max, grid$chlmean_85 - Chl_max, 0)),
                         MLD26_excess = ifelse(grid$mld26_mean < MLD_min, - MLD_min + grid$mld26_mean,
                                        ifelse(grid$mld26_mean > MLD_max, grid$mld26_mean - MLD_max, 0)),
                         MLD85_excess = ifelse(grid$mld85_mean < MLD_min, -MLD_min + grid$mld85_mean,
                                        ifelse(grid$mld85_mean > MLD_max, grid$mld85_mean - MLD_max, 0)))
